Gipsy Melody
comments: With His Majesty's Theatre Orchestra conducted by Francis M. Collinson. Though on the record label "His Majesty's Theatre Orchestra" is mentioned the recordings were actually made two weeks before the Manchester try out of Operette opened. And by the time the show opened His Majesty's Theatre in London, Collinson had been replaced by Benjamin Frankel as musical director. There was some re-orchestration and '"Gipsy Melody" was cut from the London performances.
